{"word":"H1380 - גְּבַל - Gᵉbal - gheb-al' - Gebal","slug":"H1380","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גְּבַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Gᵉbal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>gheb-al'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Gebal"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>גּבל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>gebal</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>gheb-al'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Gebal = \"mountain\" <ol><li>a maritime town of Phoenicia near Tyre (modern 'Jebeil') known to the Greeks as 'Byblus'</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1379\">H1379</a> (in the sense of a chain of hills) <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Location "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1366\">H1366</a>, <a href=\"#/H1367\">H1367</a>, <a href=\"#/H1379\">H1379</a>, <a href=\"#/H1381\">H1381</a>, <a href=\"#/H1382\">H1382</a>, <a href=\"#/H1383\">H1383</a>, <a href=\"#/H4020\">H4020</a>"}]}